# FTR-ONBOARDING – Création & switch (Customer ↔ Third-party) avec double source + “création seulement si APPROVED”

## 1. Contexte & objectif

À l’onboarding ou lors d’un **changement de type**, aligner le **set de blocs** pour le client.
**Règle clé** : si la **version courante** du bloc n’est **pas `APPROVED`**, **pas de création** de nouvelle version ; la création est autorisée **uniquement** quand la courante est `APPROVED`.
Deux sources possibles (au choix) : **T24** (snapshot JSON) **ou** **Application d’Onboarding** (operation+snapshot). Mapping vers un **évènement canonique** interne.

## 2. Portée

**In** : adapters (T24/Onb) → `PartyLifecycleEvent`, orchestrateur Party, listeners par **BlockKind**, **Approved-Gate**, `OUT_OF_SCOPE` différé si non-`APPROVED`, outbox Salesforce.
**Out** : UI, fermeture de party, suppression physique.
**Hypothèses figées** : types `{CUSTOMER, THIRD_PARTY}`, subType `IND`; matrice identique à INITLOAD.

## 3. Architecture (C4)

{plantuml}
@startuml
!include \<C4/C4\_Container>
title FTR-ONBOARDING – C4 (L2)

Person(ops, "Ops/Support")
System\_Boundary(go, "KYC Platform (GO)") {
Container(app, "GO Monolith", "Spring Modulith", "Adapters (T24/Onb), Canonicalizer, Party Orchestrator, Block Listeners(Approved-Gate), SF Outbox")
ContainerDb(db, "GO DB", "Oracle", "PARTY,BLOCK,BLOCK\_VERSION,EVENT\_INBOX,PARTY\_PROJECTION,DEFERRED\_SCOPE\_CHANGE,OUTBOX")
}
System\_Ext(t24, "T24", "Core", "JSON snapshot (key=partyId)")
System\_Ext(onb, "Onboarding App", "Domain", "operation+snapshot (key=partyId)")
System\_Ext(sf, "Salesforce", "SaaS", "Upsert bloc courant")

Rel(t24, app, "Events JSON")
Rel(onb, app, "Events op+snapshot")
Rel(app, db, "Inbox/Projection/Domain writes")
Rel(app, sf, "Outbox → Upsert", "async")
@enduml
{plantuml}

```plantuml
@startuml
title FTR-ONBOARDING – séquence Approved-Gate
actor Source
participant Adapter
database EVENT_INBOX as INB
participant Canonicalizer as CAN
participant Orchestrator as ORCH
participant "Listeners[BlockKind]" as BL
database GO_DB as DB
participant "SF Outbox" as OUT

Source -> Adapter : RawEvent{partyId, op?, snapshot, eventId, ts}
Adapter -> INB : insert(unique) or skip duplicate
Adapter -> CAN : mapToPartyLifecycleEvent()
CAN -> ORCH : handle()
ORCH -> BL : onPartyChanged(partyId,type,subType)

loop per BlockKind
  BL -> DB : read current block/version(state)
  alt Desired = IN_SCOPE
    alt current exists & state != APPROVED
      BL -> DB : NO-OP (Approved-Gate)
    else current exists & state = APPROVED
      BL -> DB : create new version if needed (INITIALIZED)
      BL -> OUT : BlockUpserted
    else no current
      BL -> DB : create block + v1 (INITIALIZED)
      BL -> OUT : BlockUpserted
    end
  else Desired = OUT_OF_SCOPE
    alt state = APPROVED
      BL -> DB : set OUT_OF_SCOPE
      BL -> OUT : BlockScopeChanged
    else state != APPROVED
      BL -> DB : record DeferredScopeChange
    end
  end
end
@enduml
```

## 5. Modèle de données (diff)

* **EVENT\_INBOX**(source, event\_id **UQ**, party\_id, event\_ts, payload\_json, status).
* **PARTY\_PROJECTION**(party\_id, last\_ts, type, subtype, status).
* **BLOCK\_VERSION**(id, block\_id, version\_no, **state** `INITIALIZED|IN_REVIEW|LOCKED|APPROVED`, valid\_from, valid\_until).
* **DEFERRED\_SCOPE\_CHANGE**(id, block\_id, target\_status=`OUT_OF_SCOPE`, reason, created\_at, applied\_at?).
* **OUTBOX**(event\_type, aggregate\_id, dedupe\_key **UQ**, payload\_json, status, retry/backoff).
* Index : `BLOCK_VERSION(block_id,state)`, `DEFERRED_SCOPE_CHANGE(block_id, applied_at)`.

## 6. Sécurité & Privacy

* RBAC par source ; secrets en vault ; logs **sans PII**.
* Schémas versionnés + DLQ en cas d’event invalide.
* STRIDE : ACL topics, audit Inbox/Outbox, backpressure.

## 7. Observabilité

* Logs décisionnels : `APPLIED|DUPLICATE|STALE|NO_OP_APPROVED_GATE|OOS_DEFERRED`.
* Métriques : `events_received/applied`, `approved_gate_noop_total`, `deferred_scope_changes`, `outbox_pending`.
* Traces : Adapter→Canonicalizer→Orchestrator→Listener.

## 8. Tests & critères d’acceptation (macro)

* Unit : mappers T24/Onb→canonique ; gate ; OOS différé.
* Intégration : Inbox idempotence ; projection temporelle.
* E2E : CREATE/ACTIVATE, SWITCH\_TO\_CUSTOMER/THIRDPARTY (avec courant APPROVED vs non).
* Non-régression : replays/out-of-order sans duplication.

